  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Urban Climate Resilience In South-Eastern Africa - Madagascar, Malawi, Mozambique And Union Of Comoros</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The revised version of the CityRAP tool, with specific enhancements linked to Urban ARK, such as through the Adaptive Capacity Index, will be subject to testing in one of the ten sub-cities of Addis Ababa. Consecutively the tool will be deployed in two municipalities in Cabo Verde, where a training of trainers will ensure maximum local capacity retention and institutionalization of good urban resilience practices. The experiences and lessons learnt will be presented and discussed during the Habitat III conference in Quito, Ecuador. Further, an academic paper and policy brief on the CityRAP tool as a mechanism for building capacity for urban risk management, with support from UN-Habitat, Future Earth Coasts (FEC) and Urban ARK teams will be developed.</narrative>
  </description>
